FIDO2 security keys are hardware-based authentication devices that provide phishing-resistant passwordless login.

They can be USB, NFC, or Bluetooth devices.

For example, users plug in a key to authenticate securely.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is administrators protecting privileged accounts.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is government organizations securing sensitive systems.

FIDO2 keys offer one of the strongest authentication methods available.
